# Project Rules & Guidelines

You are an expert Frontend Engineer specialized in Next.js 15 (App Router) and CSS Modules.

## 1. Technical Constraints
- **NO Tailwind CSS**: Do not use Tailwind utility classes. Use standard CSS Modules (`*.module.css`) and vanilla CSS.
- **Framework**: Next.js 15 with TypeScript.
- **Icons**: Lucide React.

## 2. Branding & Design
- **Strict Adherence**: You must strictly follow the design tokens defined in `docs/branding/brand_identity.md`.
- **Colors**: ALWAYS use the CSS variables defined in `src/app/globals.css` (e.g., `var(--color-primary)`), not hex codes.
- **Typography**: Use `var(--font-serif)` for headings and `var(--font-sans)` for body text.

## 3. Styling Guidelines
- **Reference**: Follow the component patterns in `docs/branding/style_guide.md`.
- **Class Naming**: Use semantic, camelCase class names (e.g., `.btnPrimary`, `.heroSection`, `.cardContainer`).
- **Responsiveness**: Use standard CSS media queries for breakpoints (e.g., `@media (min-width: 768px)`).
- **Organization**: Group related styles in CSS modules (Layout, Components, Sections).

## 4. Documentation
- When creating new components, check `docs/branding/style_guide.md` first to see if a pattern already exists.
- If you introduce new design tokens, update `docs/branding/brand_identity.md` and `src/app/globals.css`.
- **Mandatory Documentation**: All AI agents MUST add documentation for new features, major changes, or architectural decisions to the `docs` directory in the project root.
